race.comment: EVERY LITTLE THING (4) just missed at Mornington first up and then has excuses at Kyneton. Presents fitter and has plenty up her sleeve. The longer sprint suits and she's the one they have to beat. SEATTLE HOPE (6) has been plain her last two, but the Echuca and Ballarat efforts prior stack up. She's likely to show more over this distance and her best form would see her in the finish. TWINKLE VAN WINKLE (8) was tacking well before getting too far back at Tatura (vet cleared). She's another with a sticky gate but has Meech aboard, and with average luck she can be in the finish. HIDDEN WITNESS (7) has had one blip in a string of decent efforts. Has the inside gate following a freshen and goes well in that state. HIGHLAND GEORGE (5) has a soft barrier and the blinkers on for the first time and we may see more from him.
